Nonetheless, in the last few years, progress has been achieved in molecular characterization, surgical management and targeted therapies. The recent advance together with the awareness that iCCA represents a distinct entity amongst the CCA family, led the ILCA and EASL governing boards to commission and charge international experts to draft dedicated guidelines to aid physicians towards an evidence-based approach for the diagnostic, prognostic, and therapeutic management of iCCA.
